British American Tobacco P.l.c. (BTI) Receives An Update From Brokers


 By Ashley Brown /  in  Stocks /  on  Friday, 21 Jul 2017 06:21 AM  / 0 Comments




Analysts reviewing British American Tobacco p.l.c. have recently updated their recommended buy/sell ratings and price targets on the stock.  			         



Based on their most recently released notes to investors, 2 analysts have a rating of “buy”, 0 analysts “outperform”, 0 analysts “hold”, 0 analysts “underperform” and 0 analysts “sell”.
Ratings and price target breakdown:
 05/25/2017 – Piper Jaffray began new coverage on British American Tobacco p.l.c. giving the company a “” rating. They now have a USD 59 price target on the stock.
 03/06/2017 – British American Tobacco p.l.c. was upgraded to “” by analysts at Argus. They now have a USD 72 price target on the stock.
 01/06/2017 – British American Tobacco p.l.c. was upgraded to “” by analysts at RBC Capital.
 11/02/2016 – British American Tobacco p.l.c. was upgraded to “” by analysts at Morgan Stanley.
 10/28/2016 – British American Tobacco p.l.c. was upgraded to “” by analysts at Societe Generale.
 10/24/2016 – British American Tobacco p.l.c. had its “” rating reiterated by analysts at Goldman Sachs.
 09/08/2016 – British American Tobacco p.l.c. was upgraded to “” by analysts at Investec.
 07/07/2016 – British American Tobacco p.l.c. had its “” rating reiterated by analysts at Berenberg Bank.
 01/28/2016 – UBS began new coverage on British American Tobacco p.l.c. giving the company a “” rating.
 08/25/2015 – Cowen began new coverage on British American Tobacco p.l.c. giving the company a “” rating.
 08/04/2015 – Bank of America Merrill Lynch began new coverage on British American Tobacco p.l.c. giving the company a “” rating.
 06/22/2015 – Barclays began new coverage on British American Tobacco p.l.c. giving the company a “” rating.
 06/16/2015 – British American Tobacco p.l.c. was upgraded to “” by analysts at Credit Agricole.
 06/16/2015 – British American Tobacco p.l.c. had its “” rating reiterated by analysts at Credit Suisse.
 12/23/2014 – British American Tobacco p.l.c. was upgraded to “” by analysts at Zacks. They now have a USD 111.4 price target on the stock.
British American Tobacco p.l.c. has a 50 day moving average of 69.87 and a 200 day moving average of 78.48. The stock’s market capitalization is 130.15B, it has a 52-week low of 52.71 and a 52-week high of 130.40. 
The share price of the company (BTI) was up +0.86%, with a high of 70.53 during the day and the volume of British American Tobacco p.l.c. shares traded was 4020941.  



British American Tobacco p.l.c. is a tobacco and next generation products company. The Company’s tobacco product range includes cigarettes, fine cut (roll-your-own and make-your-own tobacco) and Swedish-style snus. Its segments include Asia-Pacific, Americas, Western Europe, and Eastern Europe, Middle East and Africa (EEMEA). The Asia-Pacific segment includes its operations in various countries, including Australia, Pakistan, Malaysia, Vietnam, Japan, South Korea, Indonesia, New Zealand and Bangladesh. The Americas segment includes its operations in various countries, including Brazil, Mexico, Canada, Colombia, Argentina, Chile and Venezuela. The Western Europe segment includes its operations in various countries, including Germany, Denmark, Switzerland, Belgium, France, the United Kingdom, Romania, Spain, Italy, Poland and Croatia/Balkans. The EEMEA segment includes its operations in various countries, including Russia, Ukraine, South Africa, Turkey, Egypt, Nigeria and Algeria.


